ibold text-white font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hakeem Lesolang\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hypnotherapist \\u0026 Peak Performance Coach\\\"}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-16 h-px bg-[#d4af37]/30 mb-12\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-custom\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"If one or both partners have ADHD — diagnosed or not — your relationship is playing on a different field. Not a worse field. Not a lesser field. But one with different rules, different terrain, and different requirements for success. And nobody gave you the rulebook.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"I see this constantly. A couple comes in. One partner is frustrated, hurt, convinced their partner doesn't care. The other partner is confused, defensive, genuinely baffled about why their love isn't landing. And underneath it all, undiagnosed or poorly understood ADHD is silently reshaping every interaction.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Neuroscience of the ADHD Brain in Relationships\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"ADHD is not a deficit of attention. It's a dysregulation of attention, driven by differences in dopamine and norepinephrine signaling in the prefrontal cortex. The ADHD brain doesn't lack the ability to focus — it lacks the ability to \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003edirect\\u003c/em\\u003e focus on demand. It's a brain that runs on interest, novelty, urgency, and challenge rather than importance, obligation, and routine.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In a relationship context, this creates a pattern I see over and over:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eThe Hyperfocus Phase.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Early in the relationship, the ADHD partner is all in. Texts constantly. Plans elaborate dates. Remembers every detail. The novelty and intensity of new love provides exactly the dopamine stimulation the ADHD brain craves. Their partner feels like the centre of the universe.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"12\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eThe Normalisation Phase.\\u003c/strong\\u003e As the relationship settles into routine — as it must — the dopamine reward of novelty decreases. The ADHD partner's attention naturally redistributes across multiple stimuli. They forget conversations. They lose track of commitments. They start a project and abandon it. They're present but not \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003epresent.\\u003c/em\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"14\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eThe Resentment Phase.\\u003c/strong\\u003e The non-ADHD partner, who experienced the hyperfocus as their partner's \\\\\\\"real\\\\\\\" self, now feels abandoned. \\\\\\\"They used to be so attentive. What changed? Do they not love me anymore?\\\\\\\" Meanwhile, the ADHD partner feels confused and criticised. \\\\\\\"I'm right here. I love you. Why is nothing I do enough?\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"16\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is the ADHD relationship cycle. And without understanding, it will destroy even the most loving partnership.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"18\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Executive Function Gap\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"20\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Dr. Russell Barkley, one of the world's leading ADHD researchers, describes ADHD as fundamentally a disorder of executive function — the cognitive abilities that allow you to plan, organise, prioritise, manage time, regulate emotions, and sustain effort toward goals.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"22\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In relationships, executive function deficits show up as:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"24\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eForgetting important dates, conversations, and commitments.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Not because they don't care, but because working memory is impaired. The information was encoded but not stored in a retrievable way.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"26\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eTime blindness.\\u003c/strong\\u003e The ADHD brain processes time differently. \\\\\\\"I'll be there in ten minutes\\\\\\\" might genuinely feel accurate even when it's going to take forty. This isn't lying — it's a neurological difference in temporal processing.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"28\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eEmotional dysregulation.\\u003c/strong\\u003e This is the most misunderstood aspect of ADHD in relationships. The ADHD brain experiences emotions more intensely and has less capacity to modulate them. Frustration becomes rage. Disappointment becomes despair. Excitement becomes mania. The non-ADHD partner often feels like they're living with emotional unpredictability.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eDifficulty with routine maintenance.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Chores, bills, meal planning, household logistics — the \\\\\\\"boring\\\\\\\" infrastructure of shared life runs on executive function. When one partner consistently drops the ball, the other becomes the default manager, building resentment brick by brick.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Parent-Child Dynamic (And How to Destroy It)\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The most corrosive pattern in ADHD relationships is the parent-child dynamic. The non-ADHD partner gradually takes on more and more organisational responsibility — reminding, managing, tracking, checking — until the relationship feels less like a partnership and more like a caretaking arrangement.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"36\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The non-ADHD partner feels exhausted and resentful: \\\\\\\"I have to manage everything. I didn't sign up to be their parent.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"38\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The ADHD partner feels infantilised and ashamed: \\\\\\\"They treat me like I'm incompetent. I'm not a child.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"40\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Both are right. And both are trapped in a dynamic that neither chose and neither knows how to exit.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"42\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The way out begins with understanding that this dynamic is a systemic response to unmanaged ADHD, not a character indictment of either partner. The non-ADHD partner didn't become controlling — they adapted to a vacuum. The ADHD partner didn't become irresponsible — their executive function deficits went unaccommodated.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"44\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Practical Neuroscience-Based Strategies\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"46\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e1. Externalise organisation.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Remove the need for executive function wherever possible. Shared digital calendars with alarms. Automated bill payments. Visual task boards. Meal planning apps. The goal is to build systems that don't rely on either partner's memory.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"48\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e2. Understand the dopamine reality.\\u003c/strong\\u003e The ADHD brain needs novelty and stimulation. In relationship terms, this means routine date nights should include variety and surprise. Novel experiences together — new restaurants, new activities, travel — aren't luxury. They're neurological maintenance.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"50\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e3. Time-box difficult conversations.\\u003c/strong\\u003e The ADHD brain struggles with open-ended emotional discussions. \\\\\\\"We need to talk\\\\\\\" is a cortisol bomb for an ADHD nervous system. Instead: \\\\\\\"I want to talk about the holiday plans for fifteen minutes after dinner. Is that okay?\\\\\\\" Bounded, predictable, manageable.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"52\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e4. Medication is not optional (if indicated).\\u003c/strong\\u003e I'm going to be direct here: if ADHD is significantly impacting your relationship, appropriate medication is not a luxury or a crutch. It is a neurological correction that provides the dopamine and norepinephrine support the brain needs to execute the very functions relationships require. Medication doesn't fix everything, but it creates the neurological foundation on which skills can be built.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"54\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e5. Separate the person from the symptom.\\u003c/strong\\u003e This is the NLP reframe that changes everything. \\\\\\\"My partner forgot our anniversary\\\\\\\" becomes \\\\\\\"My partner's working memory failed to consolidate a detail that matters to me.\\\\\\\" Same event. Radically different emotional response. Not because you're making excuses, but because you're making accurate attributions.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"56\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Hypnotherapy Angle\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"58\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In my work with ADHD clients, hypnotherapy serves a specific and powerful function: it addresses the shame layer that accumulates over a lifetime of being told you're lazy, careless, selfish, or \\\\\\\"not trying hard enough.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"60\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"ADHD shame is pervasive and toxic. It's the voice that says \\\\\\\"Everyone else can manage a household. What's wrong with me?\\\\\\\" It's the belief, encoded deep in the subconscious, that you are fundamentally defective. And this shame becomes a barrier to everything — seeking help, accepting support, implementing strategies, being vulnerable with your partner.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"62\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In trance, we can access that shame directly and begin to reprocess it. We can help the client differentiate between \\\\\\\"I have a brain that works differently\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\"I am broken.\\\\\\\" We can install new subconscious beliefs: \\\\\\\"I deserve support. Needing help is human. My brain's differences are real, not excuses.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"64\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"A Word to the Non-ADHD Partner\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"66\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your frustration is valid. Your exhaustion is real. You are not wrong for wanting a partner who remembers, follows through, and shares the mental load.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"68\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And — your partner is not choosing this. They are not lazy, selfish, or indifferent. They are fighting a brain that won't cooperate, often while carrying decades of shame about it.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"70\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Both truths can exist simultaneously. Your need for reliability and their neurological reality are both legitimate. The work is not to choose one truth over the other. It's to build a relationship architecture that honours both.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"72\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That is genuinely possible. I've seen it. It requires education, accommodation, and a willingness from both partners to stop blaming and start building. But the couples who do it — who learn to work \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003ewith\\u003c/em\\u003e the ADHD instead of against it — they build something remarkably strong. Because they've had to. And that intentionality becomes their superpower.\\\"}}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L16\\\",null,{\\\"title\\\":\\\"ADHD and Love: The Conversation Nobody Is Having\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"adhd-and-love-the-conversation-nobody-is-having\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L17\\\",null,{}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-[#d4af37]/30 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#d4af37]/10 to-transparent p-8 text-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold text-white font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Ready to talk about what you just read?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-2 text-sm text-[#a0aec0] font-sans max-w-md mx-auto\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Book a free discovery call with Hakeem Lesolang. No pressure. No pitch. Just an honest conversation about where you are and where you want to be.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://calendly.com/folasessions/discovery-call\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#d4af37] text-[#1a365d] px-6 py-3 rounded-xl text-sm font-bold font-sans hover:bg-[#e4bf47] transition-all hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-[#d4af37]/20\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Book Your Free Discovery Call\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"svg\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-4 h-4\\\",\\\"fill\\\":\\\"none\\\",\\\"viewBox\\\":\\\"0 0 24 24\\\",\\\"stroke\\\":\\\"currentColor\\\",\\\"strokeWidth\\\":2.5,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"path\\\",null,{\\\"strokeLinecap\\\":\\\"round\\\",\\\"strokeLinejoin\\\":\\\"round\\\",\\\"d\\\":\\\"M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6\\\"}]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-full h-px bg-white/10 my-16\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L15\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/the-uncommon-practice/the-gottman-research-most-therapists-ignore\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 hover:border-[#d4af37]/30 transition-all\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans mb-1\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Previous\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-white font-serif group-hover:text-[#d4af37] transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Gottman Research Most Therapists Ignore\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L15\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/the-uncommon-practice/trauma-is-not-what-happened-to-you\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 hover:border-[#d4af37]/30 transition-all sm:text-right\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans mb-1\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Next\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-white font-serif group-hover:text-[#d4af37] transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Trauma Is Not What Happened to You\\\"}]]}]]}]]}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"footer\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"border-t border-white/10\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-center sm:text-left\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-white font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Oasis by FOLA\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans mt-1\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"R600 per assessment\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"nav\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-6\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L15\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/the-uncommon-practice\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#a0aec0] hover:text-white transition-colors font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Uncommon Practice\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L15\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/assessment\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#d4af37] hover:text-[#e4bf47] transition-colors font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Take Assessment\\\"}]]}]]}]}]}]]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"a:null\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"e:[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"charSet\\\":\\\"utf-8\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"viewport\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\\\"}]]\\n9:null\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"c:{\\\"metadata\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"title\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"ADHD and Love: The Conversation Nobody Is Having | The Uncommon Practice\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"description\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"If one or both partners have ADHD, your relationship is playing on a different field. Not a worse one. But one with different rules that nobody taught you.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/favicon.ico\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/x-icon\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"16x16\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"3\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/icon-16.png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"16x16\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/icon-32.png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"32x32\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"5\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/icon-192.png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"192x192\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/icon-512.png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"512x512\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"link\\\",\\\"7\\\",{\\\"rel\\\":\\\"apple-touch-icon\\\",\\\"href\\\":\\\"/apple-icon.png\\\",\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"180x180\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"image/png\\\"}]],\\\"error\\\":null,\\\"digest\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}\\n14:{\\\"metadata\\\":\\\"$c:metadata\\\",\\\"error\\\":null,\\\"digest\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}\\n\"])</script></body></html>","rscData":"","headers":{"x-nextjs-stale-time":"300","x-nextjs-prerender":"1","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/the-uncommon-practice/layout,_N_T_/the-uncommon-practice/[slug]/layout,_N_T_/the-uncommon-practice/[slug]/page,_N_T_/the-uncommon-practice/adhd-and-love-the-conversation-nobody-is-having"}}}